shrapnel
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:coppers; occas. any small change; also UK rats and mice -->ca1914-18 C.R.Carr. `Shrapnel-shell comprises copper fragments held together by heavy iron bands. `Coppers' are heavy and rattle like shrapnel fragments, and were not much more valuable. Quite often pennies were referred to as `the iron'.'
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:cf. iron
Pronunciation:
Notes: Dominic says he knows this from late 1980s especially Auckland and Dunedin
